<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910712-0135</DOCNO><DOCID>910712-0135.</DOCID><HL>   Alcan Reports Loss   For Second Quarter   Totaling $5 Million</HL><DATE>07/12/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C10</SO><CO>   AL T.AL</CO><MS>BASIC MATERIALS (BSC)</MS><IN>ALUMINUM (ALU)EARNINGS (ERN)ALL NON-FERROUS METALS (NFR)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>AUSTRALIA (ASA)BRAZIL (BR)CANADA (CN)EUROPE (EU)FAR EAST (FE)GERMANY (GE)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)SOUTH AMERICA (SM)GREAT BRITAIN (UK)WESTERN EUROPE (WEU)</RE><LP>   MONTREAL -- Battered by weak aluminum prices and problemsin Brazil, Alcan Aluminium Ltd. reported a second-quarterloss of $5 million, or four cents a share on revenue of $2.02billion.   In the year-earlier period Alcan had net income of $84million, or 35 cents a share, on revenue of $2.15 billion.Alcan said results for the latest quarter include one-timecharges of $17 million, or eight cents a share related towork force reductions and the write-down of certaininvestments.</LP><TEXT>   Alcan's second-quarter loss was in line with analysts'expectations and follows a loss in the first quarter. Alcanwas quoted at $20, down 25 cents in late New York StockExchange trading.   While shipments rose slightly in the second quarter, Alcansaid prices were substantially lower than a year ago. Thealuminum concern said realized prices for aluminum ingotaveraged $1,434 a metric ton in the latest quarter comparedwith $1,628 a metric ton a year earlier. Alcan said realizedprices for fabricated aluminum products averaged $3,526 ametric ton in the quarter compared with $3,768 a metric ton ayear earlier. A metric ton equals 2,204.62 pounds.   Alcan was also hurt by Brazil's continuing economicproblems. Alcan's said its operations there had a loss of $33million in the quarter compared with break-even results ayear ago. Alcan said that profits in the Pacific regiondropped from a year earlier, due mainly to lower earnings inAustralia. In Europe, Alcan said results in Germany werestrong while the performance of its British operationsdeteriorated.   For the six months Alcan had a loss of $6 million, orseven cents a share, compared with net income of $256million, or $1.09 a share, a year earlier. Revenues were$3.97 billion compared with $4.27 billion. The 1990 six-monthperiod included one-time gains of $63 million, or 28 cents ashare.</TEXT></DOC>